						<div class="postbody">Alrighty, update!<br />After a good 1 week of failing and only getting so close that I actually made a turbo controller out of the basic one, I decided to go ahead and use the code from tepples. (Thanks for that!) It still involved a tiny bit of work because I had to chop the code up and spread the pieces across the last two banks, so that I could avoid having to lose any space for samples.<br /><br />Before moving on to creating the DPCM player, I'll try to remove everything second controller-related (that'll be a thing...) on one hand because this way players won't be able to use the cheat features, plus I'll get a few bytes in the zero page to work with in my player routine.<br /><br />Please don't help me with this unless I'm tearing my hair out. The whole point of this should be that I figure things out myself, which I've already failed at doing.<br /><br />EDIT:Oh, never mind, that was pathetically easy. Right! Now comes the fun part with the DPCM samples.</div>

